        <num>CCP 227</num>
        <heading>227.  Punishment for contempt</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 227.  Punishment for contempt
A person may not be adjudged guilty of a contempt of court except for misconduct defined as such, or made punishable as such, expressly by law.
The punishment which a court may impose upon a person adjudged guilty of contempt of court is provided in R.S. 13:4611.</p>
